Package com.esri.mo2.map.draw

Classes used for rendering vector data.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
ColorScheme A logical collection of colors that can be accessed randomly for the purpose of generating randomly colored Symbols within the draw package.
GroupRenderer Draws a FeatureClass using a list of renderers.
LabelRenderer Responsible for auto-drawing the labels for Features in a FeatureLayer.
LegendClass A LegendClass is a representation of a value or a Range of values within a Legend.
LegendInfo LegendInfo defines the details necessary for a TOC to be able to render the "classes" within a Legend.
Range Defines a pair of Comparable values that can be used with a ValueMapRenderer.
Renderer Responsible for drawing the Features from a FeatureLayer.
ScaleDependentRenderer A ScaleDependentRenderer is a wrapper for another Renderer.
SimpleRenderer A Simple Renderer is used to draw one type of Feature (Point, Line or Polygon) using a symbol.
Symbol A Symbol can be used to draw a geometry.
TextSymbol Defines the characteristics of labels associated with a Map Layer.
ValueMapRenderer A Valuemap renderer provides support for rendering based upon the value of an attribute - defined by one of the associated FeatureLayer's Fields.
 

Class Summary
AoFillStyle Stores all the predefined fill style constants and provides the corresponding Paint object by calling the appropriate getPaint method.
AoLineStroke Provides predefined line styles.
AoLineStyle Stores all the predefined line style constants and provides the corresponding Stroke object by calling the appropriate getStroke method.
AoPatternPaint Provides texture paint with predefined hatch styles.
ArcFont This special Font subclass provides additional characteristics of Underlining and Outlining.
BaseClassBreaksRenderer A ClassBreak renderer is used to draw one type of feature broken up into different breaks.
BaseFontSymbol This abstract class incapsulated a different methods to drawing text and defined constants.
BaseGroupRenderer This class uses a java.util.ArrayList for the underlying collection of sub-Renderers.
BaseLegendClass A standard implementation of LegendClass.
BaseRange A standard implementaton of the Range interface.
BaseRenderer This class can be used as a base class for your own Renderer.
BaseScaleDependentRenderer This is basic implementation of ScaleDependentRenderer interface.
BaseSimpleLabelRenderer This is an implementation of LabelRenderer that supports just one TextSymbol, in the same way that BaseSimpleRenderer does.
BaseSimpleRenderer This is a basic implementation of SimpleRenderer interface.
BaseSymbol This implementation of Symbol provides conversion between AXL and a public (shallow) clone.
BaseTextSymbol This basic implementation of a TextSymbol provides support for various appearance properties.
BaseUniqueValueRenderer This helper class provides a simple way to add LegendClasses based on single (unique) values instead of value Ranges.
BaseValueMapLabelRenderer An implementation of LabelRenderer that supports a ValueMap of TextSymbols, in the same way that BaseValueMapRenderer does.
BaseValueMapRenderer A standard implementation of the ValueMapRenderer.
CalloutMarkerSymbol Provides a simple symbol for adding labels to a Map.
ChartSymbol Displays one or more values as either a PIE or BAR chart.
ChartValue This class incapsulates the current value, lower value, upper value and color.
GradientFillSymbol The GradientFillSymbol class draws any image at the points or nodes of a given feature.
GroupSymbol A GroupSymbol is an ordered collection of Symbols.
HashLineSymbol HashlineSymbol alows to draw the railroad.
RandomColorSchemes Provides several color schemes where getNext() provides colors that are generated randomly and on-the-fly.
RandomColorSchemes.Brights produces random Colors that are bright.
RandomColorSchemes.Darks produces random Colors that are dark.
RandomColorSchemes.Pastels produces random Colors that are pastel.
RasterFillSymbol A RasterFillSymbol uses an image as a texture to draw inside a polygon.
RasterMarkerSymbol The RasterMarkerSymbol draws any image at the points or nodes of a given feature.
RasterShieldSymbol This symbol is used for drawing highway shields with a specified background image.
SampleColorSchemes Provides several indexed color schemes.
SimpleFillSymbol Deprecated. Use com.esri.mo2.map.draw.SimplePolygonSymbol instead.
SimpleLineSymbol A SimpleLineSymbol can render a Polyline using a single Stroke type and a color.
SimpleMarkerSymbol The SimpleMarkerSymbol draws markers at the points or nodes of a given feature.
SimplePolygonSymbol The SimplePolygonSymbol allows to fill the polygon features with(or without) boundary.
SimpleShieldSymbol Provides a simple symbol for adding roadway shield symbols to a map.
SimpleTextSymbol Provides a simple text to put over the map by labeling process.
TextMarkerSymbol Deprecated. This class was deprecated bacause the SimpleTextSymbol has the same functionality
TrueTypeMarkerSymbol This TrueTypeMarkerSymbol draws the character of true type font.
Util This class defines 6 default renderers and a set of convenient static methods that create various renderers based on the input parameters.
 

Exception Summary
GroupModeException This class supports message exceptions.
IllegalSymbolException Thrown in various classes if a Symbol is either null or is detected to not be a TextSymbol.
ImageLoadException Thrown within RasterMarkerSymbol if a problem occurs while loading the image.
RendererNotFoundException This class supports message exceptions.
SymbolNotFoundException This class supports message exceptions.
 

Package com.esri.mo2.map.draw Description

Classes used for rendering vector data. Symbols perform specialized rendering. Renderers organize the symbols.
